Extent 
	Subject to the following provisions of this section, this Act extends toEngland and Wales only.
	The amendment or repeal of any enactment (including an enactment comprisedin subordinate legislation) by, or in consequence of, the following provisionsof this Act has the same extent as the enactment amended or repealed—
		Part 1 (the MMO);
		Part 2 (exclusive economic zone, UK marine area and Welsh zone), other thanparagraph 2 of Schedule 4;
		Chapter 3 of Part 7 (migratory and freshwater fish);
		Chapter 4 of Part 7 (obsolete fisheries enactments);
		Part 9 (coastal access);
		in Part 10—
		sections 311 and 312 (Natural England);
		section 313 (Countryside Council for Wales);
		section 314 (which inserts Part 4A into the [Energy Act 2008 (c.32)](/id/ukpga/2008/32?view=plain "Go to item of legislation"));
		Schedule 14 (minor and consequential amendments relating to IFCauthorities).
	Subject to subsection (2)—
		any repeal in Schedule 22 (and section 321 so far as relating to therepeal) has the same extent as the provisions of this Act to which the repealrelates, but
		paragraph (a) is subject to any provision in the notes in that Schedule.
	Subject to subsection (2), the following provisions also extend toScotland—
		Part 1 (the MMO);
		Part 2 (exclusive economic zone, UK marine area and Welsh zone);
		Part 3 (marine planning);
		Part 4 (marine licensing), other than paragraph 1 of Schedule 8;
		Chapter 1 of Part 5 (MCZs), other than section 146 and Schedules 11 and 12;
		in Chapter 1 of Part 6, sections 165, 166 and 186 (powers of IFC officersetc);
		in Part 7 (fisheries)—
		sections 212 and 213 (crabs and lobsters);
		section 232 (keeping, introduction and removal of fish);
		in Part 8 (enforcement), Chapters 1 to 5 and section 295;
		this Part (other than section 321 and Schedule 22, except as provided bysubsection (2) or (3)).
	Subject to subsection (2), the following provisions also extend to NorthernIreland—
		Part 1 (the MMO);
		Part 2 (exclusive economic zone, UK marine area and Welsh zone);
		Part 3 (marine planning);
		Part 4 (marine licensing), other than paragraph 1 of Schedule 8;
		Chapter 1 of Part 5 (MCZs), other than section 146 and Schedules 11 and 12;
		in Part 8 (enforcement), Chapters 1 to 5 and section 295;
		this Part (other than section 321 and Schedule 22, except as provided bysubsection (2) or (3)).
	The amendments and repeals made by this Act to provisions of the [Food andEnvironment Protection Act 1985 (c. 48)](/id/ukpga/1985/48?view=plain "Go toitem of legislation") do not extend to any of the Channel Islands or anyBritish overseas territory.
	Her Majesty may by Order in Council—
		provide for any of the provisions of Part 4 (marine licensing) or thisPart, so far as relating to Part 4, to extend, with or without modifications,to any of the territories specified in subsection (8), and
		where any such provision is made in relation to any of those territories,repeal any provisions of Part 2 or 4 of the [Food and Environment ProtectionAct 1985](/id/ukpga/1985/48?view=plain "Go to item of legislation") (depositsin the sea etc) as they have effect as part of the law of that territory.
	The territories mentioned in subsection (7) are—
		the Bailiwick of Jersey;
		the Falkland Islands;
		South Georgia and the Sandwich Islands;
		St Helena and Dependencies.
	In section 24 of the [Sea Fish (Conservation) Act 1967 (c.84)](/id/ukpga/1967/84?view=plain "Go to item of legislation") (power toextend provisions of that Act to Isle of Man or Channel Islands), as itapplies in relation to the Bailiwick of Guernsey, any reference to a provisionof that Act includes a reference to that provision as amended by any provisionof Chapter 1 of Part 7 of this Act.
	The amendments made by—
		paragraph 2 of Schedule 4 (amendments to the [Fishery Limits Act 1976 (c.86)](/id/ukpga/1976/86?view=plain "Go to item of legislation")),
		section 212 (taking of crabs and lobsters for scientific purposes), and
		section 213 (orders prohibiting the taking and sale of certain lobsters),
			do not extend to the Isle of Man or the Channel Islands.

Commencement 
	The following provisions of this Act come into force on the day on whichthis Act is passed—
		in Part 3 (marine planning)—
		paragraphs 4(1) to (4), 5 and 6 of Schedule 5 (statement of publicparticipation relating to MPS) and, so far as relating to those paragraphs,paragraphs 1 and 2 of that Schedule;
		sections 44(1)(b) and (5) and 45(4), so far as relating to thoseparagraphs;
		this Part, other than section 321 and Schedule 22;
		any power of a Minister of the Crown, the Scottish Ministers, the WelshMinisters or a Northern Ireland department to make regulations or an orderunder or by virtue of this Act;
		any power to make an Order in Council under the [Government of Wales Act2006 (c. 32)](/id/ukpga/2006/32?view=plain "Go to item of legislation") byvirtue of the amendments made by section 43 and paragraph 6 of Schedule 4(Welsh zone).
	So far as not already brought into force by virtue of subsection (1), thefollowing provisions of this Act come into force at the end of the period of 2months beginning with the day on which this Act is passed—
		Part 3 (marine planning);
		in Part 5—
		Chapter 1 (MCZs), so far as not relating to MCZs in Wales;
		Chapter 2 (other conservation sites), so far as not relating to Wales;
		sections 190 to 193 (inshore fisheries in Wales);
		Part 9 (coastal access).
	Subject to subsection (4), the other provisions of this Act come into forceon an appointed day.
	Any repeal in Schedule 22 (and section 321 so far as relating to therepeal) comes into force in the same way as the provisions of this Act towhich the repeal relates.
	In this section “appointed day” means such day or days as the Secretary ofState may by order appoint.
	The power conferred by subsection (5) is exercisable by the Welsh Ministers(and not the Secretary of State) in relation to the following provisions—
		so far as relating to MCZs in Wales—
		Chapter 1 of Part 5 (MCZs);
		the repeals in Schedule 22 relating to that Chapter;
		section 321 so far as relating to those repeals;
		Chapter 2 of Part 5 (other conservation sites), so far as relating toWales;
		so far as relating to sea fisheries districts in Wales, or any part of asea fisheries district lying in Wales—
		in Part 6, section 187 (repeal of the [Sea Fisheries Regulation Act 1966(c. 38)](/id/ukpga/1966/38?view=plain "Go to item of legislation"));
		the repeals in Schedule 22 relating to that section;
		section 321 so far as relating to that section and those repeals.
	An order under subsection (5) may appoint different days for differentpurposes.
	In this section “Wales” includes the Welsh inshore region.
